olive oil
1 cucumber
1 tomato
½ lime
1 packet mayonnaise
1 bag slaw mix
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 packet beef strips
1 tsp honey
1 drizzle vinegar (white wine or red wine)
1 sachet South American Seasoning

• Roughly chop cucumber and tomato. Zest lime and slice into wedges.
• In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise and lime zest. Set aside.
• In a medium bowl, combine cucumber, tomato, a drizzle of vinegar and a
pinch of salt and pepper. Set aside.

• In a second medium bowl, combine slaw mix, baby spinach leaves, 1/2 the
lime mayo and a squeeze of lime juice. Season to taste. Set aside.
• In a third medium bowl, combine South American seasoning, a drizzle of
olive oil and a pinch of pepper. Add beef strips and toss to coat.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat. When oil is hot,
cook beef strips, tossing, in batches, until browned and cooked through, 1-2
minutes.
• Remove pan from heat, then add the honey and toss to coat.

TIP: Cooking the meat in batches over high heat helps it stay tender.

• Divide slaw between bowls.
• Top with South American-spiced beef strips and cucumber salsa.
• Drizzle over remaining lime mayo. Serve with any remaining lime wedges.
Enjoy!